{\plain }{\plain\f17 Apparently this help file was already compiled. Many properties of the help file can be defined in the INT2WHLP.CFG file used by the the INT2WHLP compiler available in the DOS version of Ralf Brown's Interrupt List, see }{\uldb {\f17 INTERRUP.1ST}}{\v id1st}{\plain\f17 . After compilation, only a few of them can be changed, and only utilizing special programs, see }{\uldb {\f17 Size and Color}}{\v HHsizeColor}{\plain\f17 .\par 
\par 
}{\plain\f17 The following can be controlled at compile time:\par 
\par 
}{\plain\f17 Whether the help file has both a compressed and an expanded index, or a compressed index only.\par 
\par 
}{\plain\f17 Which one of the two pops up initially.\par 
\par 
}{\plain\f17 Whether single-entry interrupts (interrupts numbers with only one topic in the list) are referenced directly from the compressed index, or the reference in the compressed index goes to a subindex with one entry.\par 
\par 
}{\plain\f17 Whether the compressed index is listed in a single column with a header for each interrupt number, or in 4, 8, or 16 columns without headers, but with more entries visible simultaniously.\par 
\par 
}{\plain\f17 Whether or not the expanded index has headers separating the interrupt numbers.\par 
\par 
}{\plain\f17 Whether or not keywords (like "See also:", "Notes") are bolded.\par 
\par 
}{\plain\f17 Whether or not long versions of interrupt search strings are enabled (see }{\uldb {\f17 Win95 WinHelp Restrictions}}{\v HHwin95}{\plain\f17 )}{\plain\f17 .\par 
\par 
}{\plain\f17 Whether or not "#nnnn" table keywords are inserted in the primary keyword table or in a secondary keyword table (see }{\uldb {\f17 Win95 WinHelp Restrictions}}{\v HHwin95}{\plain\f17 )}{\plain\f17 . The dynamic link library file seckey.dll or seckey32.dll must be available if they shall be retrieved from the secondary table.\par 
\par 
}{\plain\f17 Whether or not there are spaces around the equal sign in interrupt search strings e.g. "INT 21 AH = 4C" or "INT 21 AH=4C".\par 
\par 
}{\plain\f17 The initial position and size, and the background colors of both the main and the table window.\par 
\par 
}{\plain\f17 The font and font size used for the headers and for the text.\par 
\par 
}{\plain\f17 Extra topics included in addition to Ralf Brown's Interrupt List (like this Help and Hints text).\par 
\par 
}{\plain\f17 See also the files (in INTERnn?.ZIP/INT2WHLP.ZIP):\par 
