}{\plain\f17\fs28 Search Facilities}\par \pard\plain\s0 {\plain\f17 
}\par 
{\plain }{\plain\f17 INTWIN facilitates seaching interrupt topics with many different keys, based on:}\par 
\pard\s5\li567\fi-282 {\plain\f17 }{\plain\f17 a. Elements in the interrupt header line.\par 
}{\plain\f17 b. Keys in the file CATEGORY.KEY for the appropriate interrupts category.\par 
}{\plain\f17 c. Combinations of interrupt number and register contents. These keys have a normal and a short form. The short form was introduced to ease the typing of a search string. See the examples below.\par 
}{\plain\f17 d. Category letters.}\par 
\pard\s0 {\plain\f17 \par 
}{\plain\f17 For example,\par 
}\par 
\pard\s3\keep {\plain\f16\fs20 }{\plain\f16\fs20 --------D-215E01CH00-----------------------------\par 
}{\plain\f16\fs20 INT 21 - DOS 3.1+ network - SET MACHINE NAME\par 
}{\plain\f16\fs20 \tab }{\plain\f16\fs20 AX = 5E01h\par 
}{\plain\f16\fs20 \tab }{\plain\f16\fs20 CH = 00h undefine name (make it invalid)}\par 
\pard\s0 {\plain\f17 \par 
}{\plain\f17 will be listed with the following search keys:\par 
}\par 
\pard\s3\keep {\plain\f16\fs20 }{\plain\f16\fs20 \tab }{\plain\f16\fs20 DOS 3.1+ network            \\      a\par 
}{\plain\f16\fs20 \tab }{\plain\f16\fs20 SET MACHINE NAME            /\par 
}{\plain\f16\fs20 \tab }{\plain\f16\fs20 DOS kernal                  \\ \par 
}{\plain\f16\fs20 \tab }{\plain\f16\fs20 kernal (DOS)                 >     b\par 
}{\plain\f16\fs20 \tab }{\plain\f16\fs20 operating systems (DOS)     /\par 
}{\plain\f16\fs20 \tab }{\plain\f16\fs20 INT 21 AX = 5E01 CH = 00 5) \\\par 
}{\plain\f16\fs20 \tab }{\plain\f16\fs20 INT 21 AX = 5E01         5)  \\\par 
}{\plain\f16\fs20 \tab }{\plain\f16\fs20 INT 21 AH = 5E           5)   \\\par 
}{\plain\f16\fs20 \tab }{\plain\f16\fs20 INT 21          1)       5)    \\\par 
}{\plain\f16\fs20 \tab }{\plain\f16\fs20 21 5E01 CH00                    \\\par 
}{\plain\f16\fs20 \tab }{\plain\f16\fs20 21 5E01                          > c\par 
}{\plain\f16\fs20 \tab }{\plain\f16\fs20 21 5E           2)              /\par 
}{\plain\f16\fs20 \tab }{\plain\f16\fs20 21              1)             /\par 
}{\plain\f16\fs20 \tab }{\plain\f16\fs20 AX = 5E01                     /\par 
}{\plain\f16\fs20 \tab }{\plain\f16\fs20 AH = 5E         3)           /\par 
}{\plain\f16\fs20 \tab }{\plain\f16\fs20 CH = 00                     /\par 
}{\plain\f16\fs20 \tab }{\plain\f16\fs20 D!              4)                 d}\par 
\pard\s0 {\plain\f17 }\par 
\pard\s4\li720\fi-718 {\plain\f17 }{\plain\f17 1)}{\plain\f17 \tab }{\plain\f17 WINHELP lists only the first 400 search hits.\par 
}{\plain\f17 2)}{\plain\f17 \tab }{\plain\f17 The short form of an interrupt using AL to }{\plain\f17 specify a function has two leading dashes in the function number, e.g. the short form of INT 2D AL = 10 is 2D --10.\par 
}{\plain\f17 \tab }{\plain\f17 Two dashes can be appended to the short form of an interrupt using AH for funtion number, to distinguish the string from the more general string used also as keyword for interrupts with the same value in the high part of the AX register, e.g. 10 00-- will give less search hits than 10 00.\par 
}{\plain\f17 3)}{\plain\f17 \tab }{\plain\f17 Use AH = nn to search for functions called with nn in AH or in the high byte of AX. Use AX = nn-- to search for functions called with nn in AH and no specific value in AL.\par 
}{\plain\f17 4)}{\plain\f17 \tab }{\plain\f17 Because WINHELP's search facility does not distinguish between letter case, the search keys for capital letter categories are the letter followed by an exclamation mark.\par 
}{\plain\f17 5)}{\plain\f17 \tab }{\plain\f17 The long version of interrupt search keys can be disabled at compile time, see }{\uldb {\f17 Win95 WinHelp Restrictions}}{\v HHwin95}{\plain\f17 . In this case, topic "INT  xx Search Keys" lists examples of corresponding long and short search keys.\par 
\par 
}{\plain\f17 For table search facilities, see }{\uldb {\f17 Table Cross-References}}{\v HHtable}{\plain\f17 .}\par 
